Q. Convert feet into meters.

Write a program that reads a number in feet, converts it to meters, and displays the result.
One foor is 0.305 meter. Note: Use datatype as Double.

Solution:
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;
public class convert {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
  Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
  Double feet=s.nextDouble();
  Double m=feet*0.305;
  System.out.printf("%0.3f meters",m);
 }
}

